---
import PolicyLayout from '../../layouts/PolicyLayout.astro';
import SubpagesQuickLinks from '../../components/SubpagesQuickLinks.astro';
---

<PolicyLayout
	title="Installation & Setup"
	description="How to install Audius Song of the Day on Discord and finish setup for your account or server."
	lastUpdated={undefined}
>
	<SubpagesQuickLinks />
	<h2>Choose your install context</h2>
	<p>
		Install to a guild for a shared channel, or install to your user account
		for daily DMs.{' '}
		<a
			href="https://docs.discord.com/developers/resources/application#installation-context"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noopener noreferrer"
		>
			What's the difference?
		</a>
	</p>

	<div class="btn-row">
		<a
			href="https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=1504248701412053052&permissions=4503599627390016&integration_type=0&scope=applications.commands+bot"
			class="btn btn--primary"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noopener noreferrer"
		>
			Install to a Guild
			<span class="btn-label"
				>Post the Song of the Day in a server channel and optionally
				ping a role.</span
			>
		</a>
		<a
			href="https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=1504248701412053052&integration_type=1&scope=applications.commands"
			class="btn"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noopener noreferrer"
		>
			Install to your User Account
			<span class="btn-label"
				>Receive a daily DM with the Song of the Day.</span
			>
		</a>
		<a
			href="https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=1504248701412053052&integration_type=1&scope=applications.commands"
			class="btn"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noopener noreferrer"
		>
			Default Installation Link
			<span class="btn-label"
				>Manually configure your own settings through the Discord App
				Install flow.</span
			>
		</a>
	</div>

	<div class="callout">
		<strong>Warning:</strong> The Default Installation Link is not recommended
		for regular users. If you don't know what this does, it's safer to stick to
		the options above. If you break the installation, you may need to reinstall
		the bot which may remove your settings.
	</div>

	<h2>Finish setup</h2>
	<p>
		If you've installed to your user account, you'll need to run <code
			>/sotd subscribe</code
		> to enable DM notifications.
	</p>
	<p>
		If you've installed to a guild, choose the correct option below to
		configure the bot.
	</p>

	<h3>I've never used ASOTD before</h3>
	<p>
		After installing, run the following commands to configure the bot for
		your guild:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><code>/sotd config set-role</code></li>
		<li><code>/sotd config set-channel</code></li>
		<li><code>/sotd config set-auto-thread</code></li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		If the commands don't appear, restart your Discord client to refresh the
		command list. If they still don't appear, you may need to wait a bit for
		the Discord API to propagate the commands to your guild.
	</p>

	<h3>I've used ASOTD before and am re-installing</h3>
	<p>
		If you've uninstalled ASOTD from your guild in the last 30 days, your
		configuration is still saved. Run <code>/sotd config restore</code> to restore
		your old configuration.
	</p>
	<p>
		If it's been more than 30 days, your data has been removed as per our{
			' '
		}
		<a href="/audius-sotd/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> and you'll need to reconfigure
		from scratch:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><code>/sotd config set-role</code></li>
		<li><code>/sotd config set-channel</code></li>
		<li><code>/sotd config set-auto-thread</code></li>
	</ul>

	<h3>I don't know if I've used ASOTD before</h3>
	<p>
		Run <code>/sotd config status</code> to view your current settings. To change
		any configuration, use the commands as if it were a new installation:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><code>/sotd config set-role</code></li>
		<li><code>/sotd config set-channel</code></li>
		<li><code>/sotd config set-auto-thread</code></li>
	</ul>

	<h2>I have a question</h2>
	<p>Create a GitHub issue and we'll help you ASAP, or email directly.</p>
	<div class="btn-row">
		<a
			href="https://github.com/tobezdev/Audius-Song-of-the-Day/issues"
			class="btn"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noopener noreferrer"
		>
			⚡ Open a GitHub issue
		</a>
		<a href="mailto:toby@tobezdev.com" class="btn btn--primary">
			✉ toby@tobezdev.com
		</a>
	</div>
</PolicyLayout>
